co-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 13, 2022</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104fox1665702921225.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/fox1665702921225.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/fox1665702921225.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"fox1665702921225\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Performance\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"fox1665702921225__performance_140019\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">The performance of an application becomes an issue if users find that the application speed (elapsed time between an end-user request and the application's response) does not meet expectations or if the application is unavailable when required.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"fox1665702921225__p_d45506e1_d45507e1_d45508e1\">Performance depends on such factors as:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"fox1665702921225__li_d22682e1_d22683e1_d22684e1\">Available computing resources\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"fox1665702921225__li_d22685e1_d22686e1_d22687e1\">System load\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"fox1665702921225__li_d22688e1_d22689e1_d22690e1\">System efficiency\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"fox1665702921225__li_d22691e1_d22692e1_d22693e1\">Concurrency\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"fox1665702921225__li_d22694e1_d22695e1_d22696e1\">Transaction complexity\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"fox1665702921225__li_d22697e1_d22698e1_d22699e1\">Rush hour processing\n </li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"fox1665702921225__p_d45509e1_d45510e1_d45511e1\">In practice, there might be only a limited budget for optimizing performance, so it makes sense to first address those issues with the highest impact on performance.</p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"fox1665702921225__topic_d29552e1_d29553e1_d29554e1_d29555e1_d29556e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d201494e81\">\n           \n Performance Optimization Checklist\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"fox1665702921225__p_d45515e1_d45516e1_d45517e1\">The following checklist presents the areas of interest based on their impact on performance. The order is not absolute and you might want to reconsider it for your particular circumstances. For example, database indexes and layout of entities are related to data design, so you might consider them together. However, as a general rule, it is recommended that you examine the issues in the following order:</p>\n<ol class=\"ol\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"fox1665702921225__li_d22700e1_d22701e1_d22702e1\">Expectations regarding response times\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"fox1665702921225__li_d22703e1_d22704e1_d22705e1\">Available computing resources\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"fox1665702921225__li_d22706e1_d22707e1_d22708e1\">System load balancing—See <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"prf1665702921294.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/prf1665702921294.html\" title=\"Load balancing entails distributing the application components, databases, servers, and processing to make best use of the available resources. This can affect both where application files are located and when processing takes place.\">Load Balancing</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"fox1665702921225__li_d22709e1_d22710e1_d22711e1\">Data design—See <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"tro1665702921363.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/tro1665702921363.html\" title=\"Before modeling the data and relationships, you should create a design. You should identify which data is used most frequently and the paths that are used to access the data. This information is required to define the optimal data model. This is not necessarily the ideal data model, because it might contain redundant data to better meet performance requirements.\">Data Design</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"fox1665702921225__li_d22712e1_d22713e1_d22714e1\">Process contention—See <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"wux1665702922021.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/wux1665702922021.html\" title=\"Concurrent processes might simultaneously allocate the same resources, such as certain parts of internal memory or specific rows of a table. Intensive use of the same resources by various processes cause contention and can decrease performance. In such situations, it is worthwhile to rearrange the application architecture so the required resources are allocated more selectively. An obvious way to do this is to reconsider the transaction definitions by minimizing the locking periods, the amount of locked data, or both.\">Performance Contention</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"fox1665702921225__li_d22715e1_d22716e1_d22717e1\">Component logic—See <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"rip1665702922090.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rip1665702922090.html\" title=\"Even with an optimized application model, there are still design and implementation decisions that can affect performance, such as your choice of components, data retrieval implementation, component data structure and indexing decisions.\">Performance Guidelines for Component Logic and Implementation</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"fox1665702921225__li_d22718e1_d22719e1_d22720e1\">Component implementation—See Component logic\n            </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"fox1665702921225__li_d22721e1_d22722e1_d22723e1\">Database indexes\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"fox1665702921225__li_d22724e1_d22725e1_d22726e1\">Choice of components—See <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ypn1665702922162.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ypn1665702922162.html\" title=\"Your choice of implementation technology and the way in which the component is implemented can affect performance.\">Component Implementations and Performance</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"fox1665702921225__li_d22727e1_d22728e1_d22729e1\">Swapping\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"fox1665702921225__li_d22730e1_d22731e1_d22732e1\">Web servers\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"fox1665702921225__li_d22733e1_d22734e1_d22735e1\">DBMS tuning—See <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"bjy1665702922231.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/bjy1665702922231.html\" title=\"The DBMS is the system layer that an application must access directly. Uniface interacts with a DBMS via a DBMS-specific connector. The DBMS contributes to the system load, so it is an area of interest for performance optimization.\">Database Tuning</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"fox1665702921225__li_d22736e1_d22737e1_d22738e1\">Operating system and the network\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"fox1665702921225__li_d22739e1_d22740e1_d22741e1\">Layout of entities—See <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"uvu1665702922300.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/uvu1665702922300.html\" title=\"The choices you make in ordering and indexing entity fields can have a negative impact on performance.\">Layout of Entities and Fields</a>\n</li>\n</ol>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527603\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527603\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Performance Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 13, 2022 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Performance The performance of an application becomes an issue if users find that the application speed (elapsed time between an end-user request and the application's response) does not meet expectations or if the application is unavailable when required. Performance depends on such factors as: Available computing resources System load System efficiency Concurrency Transaction complexity Rush hour processing In practice, there might be only a limited budget for optimizing performance, so it makes sense to first address those issues with the highest impact on performance. Performance Optimization Checklist The following checklist presents the areas of interest based on their impact on performance. The order is not absolute and you might want to reconsider it for your particular circumstances. For example, database indexes and layout of entities are related to data design, so you might consider them together. However, as a general rule, it is recommended that you examine the issues in the following order: Expectations regarding response times Available computing resources System load balancing—See Load Balancing Data design—See Data Design Process contention—See Performance Contention Component logic—See Performance Guidelines for Component Logic and Implementation Component implementation—See Component logic Database indexes Choice of components—See Component Implementations and Performance Swapping Web servers DBMS tuning—See Database Tuning Operating system and the network Layout of entities—See Layout of Entities and Fields Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}